excerpt: Elaborate palace & mausoleum with ornate details like multiple minarets featuring spiral staircases.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Junagadh, Mahabat Maqbara Palace stands as a stunning testament to the grandeur of 19th-century architecture. This elaborate mausoleum, originally constructed as a residence for the Babi Nawabs, showcases an exquisite fusion of Indo-Islamic and Gothic styles. As you step through its majestic arches, you're greeted by intricate jali work and dazzling Venetian glass interiors that transport you back to an era filled with royal splendor.
name: Mahabat Maqbara Palace
address: Junagadh - Mendarda Hwy, Mullawada, Junagadh, Gujarat 362001, India

excerpt: Longtime zoo featuring a variety of animals, including endangered Asian lions & other rare species.
detail_description: Nestled in the heart of Junagadh, Gujarat, Sakkarbaug Zoological Park is a historical gem that has been captivating visitors since its inception in 1863. Originally established as a small menagerie for the Nawab of Junagadh, this sprawling 200-hectare wildlife sanctuary has evolved into one of the region's most cherished attractions.
name: Sakkarbaug Zoological Park
address: Rajkot Hwy, Joshipura, Junagadh, Gujarat 362001, India

excerpt: Holy lake with a temple & idols, revered by Hindus for bathing & immersing bones of the dead.
detail_description: Nestled at the base of the majestic Girnar hills in Junagadh, Gujarat, Damodar Kund is a revered holy lake steeped in Hindu tradition. This sacred site draws many devotees who come to bathe and immerse the ashes and bones of their loved ones, believing that doing so grants moksha to departed souls. The tranquil waters of this 257-foot-long and 50-foot-wide lake are thought to possess unique properties that aid in dissolving remains.
name: Damodar Kund

detail_description: Girnar Ashoka Rock Edicts are a significant collection of inscriptions made by Emperor Ashoka during his reign from 268 BCE to 232 BCE. Located on the Saurashtra peninsula of Junagadh in Gujarat, these inscriptions are considered some of the most important among Ashoka's edicts. They are inscribed in Brahmi script, which is believed to be the oldest script used in India.
name: Girnar Ashoka Rock Edicts
address: GFGH+2QP, WAY TOWORDS "UPALE VAGHESHWARI MA" By STEPS, Bhavnath Taleti Rd, opp. sonapuri, Junagadh, Gujarat 362001, India

excerpt: Imposing ancient fort, dating to c. 319 BC, with towering ramparts, Buddhist caves & 15th-c. mosque.
detail_description: Uparkot Fort, a magnificent relic of history dating back to around 319 BC, stands as a testament to the architectural prowess of its time. Originally constructed by the Mauryan emperor Chandragupta, this fort has been expanded over centuries and features impressive ramparts that soar up to 20 meters high. It has withstood numerous siegesâ€”legend even tells of a remarkable 12-year siege!
name: Uparkot Fort

detail_description: Moti Baug, also known as the Pearl Garden, is a tranquil botanical park nestled within the bustling city of Junagadh in Gujarat, India. Situated on the grounds of Junagadh Agricultural University, this lush oasis was established in memory of Nawab Muhammad Mahabat Khanji III's beloved pet dog. The garden boasts vibrant flora and verdant lawns, offering a serene escape for visitors.
name: Moti Baug

detail_description: Navghan Kuvo, a nearly thousand-year-old step well, is a unique structure partially carved out of soft rock and partly built up like other wells. Its 52-meter-deep shaft features stairs wrapping around it, making it an unusual sight. The water from Navghan Kuvo sustained Uparkot through prolonged sieges. Located in Junagadh near the famous Gir National Park, this historical gem has recently undergone impressive renovations, showcasing its captivating history and remarkable restoration work.
name: Navghan Kuvo

detail_description: Nestled within the historic landscape of Junagadh, Adi Kadi Vav is a captivating stepwell that showcases the remarkable engineering skills of ancient India. Carved from solid sandstone nearly a thousand years ago, this architectural gem features an impressive descent of 120 steps leading to its depths. As you navigate through the intricately designed staircases, you'll be enveloped in a mesmerizing play of light and shadow that dances across the stone surfaces.
name: Adi Kadi Vav

detail_description: Khapara Kodiya Caves, part of the Junagadh Buddhist Cave Group in Gujarat, India, are the oldest caves dating back to 3rd-4th century BCE. These ancient rock-cut caves hold religious and historical significance for Jains and Hindus. The site features intricate sculptures and carvings showcasing the artistic prowess of that era.
name: Khapara Kodiya Caves

detail_description: Jama Masjid is one of the must-visit attractions in Junagadh, surrounded by other tourist spots like Mahabat Maqbara and Mount Girnar. name: Jama Masjid

detail_description: Nestled at the foothills of Girnar Hill, Bhavnath Mahadev Temple is a revered Hindu pilgrimage site in Gujarat. The temple's sacred Shivling is believed to have manifested on its own. Visitors also praise the spiritual ambiance and the nearby Mrugi Kund, home to an abundance of fish and turtles.
name: Bhavnath Mahadev Temple

address: Taj Manzil Building, Nagar Road, Duruvesh Nagar, Shashikunj, Durvesh, Junagadh, Gujarat 362001, India

address: Taj Manzil Building, Nagar Road, Duruvesh Nagar, Shashikunj, Durvesh, Junagadh, Gujarat 362001, India
